    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REMOVE - LEFT REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY
        (FIGURE 45)
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="8">
        <title>LEFT REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY (
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1302145">FIGURE 45</hotlnk>)
        </title>
        <figure id="f1302145" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1302145" filename="../figg13/G1302145.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 45. Left Reverse Idler Gear Assembly</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move the mainshaft reverse gear as far to the rear as possible and remove the snap ring from
                the I.D. of the gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302146">Figure 46</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302146" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302146" filename="../figg13/G1302146.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. Remove Snap Ring</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the idler shaft plug from the rear of the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302147">Figure 47</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302147" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302147" filename="../figg13/G1302147.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. Idler Shaft Plug</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the front countershaft bearing race (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302148">Figure 48</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302148" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302148" filename="../figg13/G1302148.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Front Countershaft Bearing Race</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Loosen the reverse idler shaft nut (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302149">left, Figure 49</hotlnk>). Remove the nut and washer from the shaft (right).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302149" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302149" filename="../figg13/G1302149.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. Reverse Idler Shaft Nut</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Move reverse gear forward against LO gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302150">Figure 50</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302150" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302150" filename="../figg13/G1302150.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. Reverse Gear Forward</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Use an impact puller, 1/2-13 threaded end, to remove the idler shaft from the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302151">Figure 51</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302151" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302151" filename="../figg13/G1302151.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. Remove Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">As the idler shaft and washer are removed to the rear, remove the (2) thrust washers and
                gear from the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1302152">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1302152" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302152" filename="../figg13/G1302152.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. Remove Thrust Washers</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
